President Donald Trump has issued a proclamation declaring October 21-27, 2018 as National Forest Products Week. In the proclamation, he highlights the importance of forests in the American economy and recognizes the forest products industry as one of the top 10 manufacturing sector employers in 45 states. He also emphasizes the need for effective, science-based forest management to support the industry and promote job growth. The proclamation encourages Americans to appreciate the contributions of forests and woodlands to everyday life and to participate in activities that celebrate and protect these natural resources.